  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>sweet</strong> <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skin on) into thin chips, then add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the chips are golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-garlic-free-range-chicken-and-apple-remoulade-sandwich/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dice your <strong>apple[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>(skin on) finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-garlic-free-range-chicken-and-apple-remoulade-sandwich/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> free range chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to a chopping board and cover with a sheet of <strong>cling film</strong>, then bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until evenly flattened</p><p>Pat dry with kitchen paper – this is your <strong>chicken escalope</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-garlic-free-range-chicken-and-apple-remoulade-sandwich/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a shallow bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>garlic panko</strong></p><p>Turn the <strong>chicken escalope[s]</strong> in the <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>panko</strong> until fully coated – this is your <strong>garlic panko chicken</strong></p><p>Tip: Press the chicken into the breadcrumbs firmly to coat evenly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-garlic-free-range-chicken-and-apple-remoulade-sandwich/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> garlic panko chicken</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side, or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy garlic free range chicken</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if the pan looks a little dry</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-garlic-free-range-chicken-and-apple-remoulade-sandwich/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your<strong> ciabatta[s]</strong> to a baking tray and pop the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-garlic-free-range-chicken-and-apple-remoulade-sandwich/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Separate 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>outer leaves </strong>per person from the<strong> lettuce</strong>, wash the leaves and pat dry with kitchen paper, then set them aside for serving</p><p>Cut the <strong>inner core[s] </strong>into quarters</p><p>Combine the <strong>diced apple</strong>, <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and<strong> chopped parsley</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>sugar </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>apple</strong> <strong>remoulade</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-garlic-free-range-chicken-and-apple-remoulade-sandwich/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> warmed ciabatta[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Fill the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>ciabatta halves </strong>with the<strong> lettuce leaves</strong>, <strong>apple</strong> <strong>remoulade</strong> and <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>garlic free range chicken</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>sweet potato chips</strong> and <strong>lettuce quarters</strong> to the side</p><p>Dollop any <strong>remaining apple remoulade </strong>over the<strong> </strong>lettuce quarters</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
